I changed the statement according to which Ahmed's marked an end in this tradition because it is simply not true. Ahmed did not kill his brother Mustafa, but fratricide in the ottoman dynasty did not come to an end until the reign of Ibrahim. Osman II killed his oldest brother Mehmet before his first campaign and Murad IV killed three of his four remaining brothers, leaving only Ibrahim. This is all in page 101 and 102 of  Leslie Pierce's book The Imperial Harem, the exact one previously cited

Nazenin/Veleria Hatun is a fictional character from Muhteshem Yuzyil. It is not historically clear who the mother of Raziye Sultan was. Since Sultan Suleiman never married anyone apart from Hurrem and Raziye is certainly not recorded among Hurrems offspring, Raziye is the daughter of an unknown concubine. She probably died with her elder brothers Mahmud and Murad in 1521.
